<br>
Pizza:<br>
<br>
My favorite stupid question in the world when I was at Domino's<br>
<br>
&quot;How many slices in your large pizza?&quot;<br>
&quot;8&quot;<br>
&quot;How many slices in your medium?&quot;<br>
&quot;8&quot;<br>
Long pause<br>
&quot;well then what's the difference?&quot;<br>
I just wanna say &quot;nothing we just charge more.&quot;<br>
<br>
Movies:<br>
<br>
1.  It says no outside food and drink.  Don't argue just do it.  This serves two purposes.  Technically we are an eating establishment.  Try to take McDonalds into ur avg restaurant.  You'll get told no.  It's against the health dept rules.  Secondly most people don't know this but movie theatres don't make dick on a ticket.  On a typical opening weekend we'll make 60-90 cents per ticket.  The rest goes back to the studio.  So they have to inflate prices and keep food out to survive.<br>
<br>
2.  Don't show up to a fucking sold out show 10 min after it starts and complain that you can't get a good seat.  Use ur fucking brain. <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=272425</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bdrinal28133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=magadi>magadi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#33cc33>Drinalite</font></span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/02 5:10:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1694.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pizza and Movies</span><hr size=1> People in restaurants are very much people in EQ. (People are people are people) Some are nice and curteous, some think the world owes them something and everyone is out to screw them over.<br>
<br>
Seriously<br>
<br>
I worked as a waitress through college, I've had my fill of people being impatient, being demanding when I've had 8+ tables (of 3-6 people each) and people forgetting to tell me that they are allergic to peanuts after I tell them the special INCLUDES peanut sauce and have them "talk" to my manager after they order it! I mean WTF! <br>
<br>
I loved being a waitress, very few professions get to work with people and chat with them and have fun while getting money. But there are some people that just DONT GET IT! I've had the pleasure of "accidentally" spilling a tray of drinks (worked as a bar waitress for awhile) on a particularly idiotic customer, and the bouncers nearby just laughed and kicked the guy out. (LOVED THAT!)<br>
<br>
I have to say that I've been lucky in the serving business however, one day, I was waiting tables as usual, and two big gentlemen and one smaller sized gentlemen came in and were chatty and very nice and tipped well. I wasn't that busy so I talked with them about music (the smaller gentleman was a drummer) and places to see around the area etc. Half hour later they came in and said "Maggy, can we sit in your section?" I was like... um... you ate already why you back here? But money is money and good customers are good customers and the manager was nice and let me take their table even though my section was full. I noticed they had someone with them they didn't have before with a hood on and dark glasses. Whatever, maybe they thought the food was good and their friend was hungry. So I seat them offer them something to drink and the lady takes off her hood and glasses....<br>
<br>
Hello Sarah McLachlen!<br>
<br>
OMFG!<br>
<br>
The drummer guy was apparently her husband and liked the atmosphere so much he brought her back with him so she didn't have to eat at the hotel. Needless to say (I'm a chic so I listen to her stuff and love it) I was floored. Even better she ordered and eggnog and asked me to sit down and share it with her. <br>
<br>
OMFG!<br>
<br>
Haha I was starstruck, and she was a VERY nice customer and tipped very well. I wouldn't have ever had that experience in any other profession that I could get into easily. <br>
<br>
So you see, people suck, but if you suck accidentally spill drinks on you and get a better customer later :)<br>
<br>
